reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good mouthwash, not so good packets.
reviews.reviewText: Ingredients: Water, Sorbitol, PEG-40 hydrogenated castor oil, Betaine, Propyglycol, Xylitol, Potassium sorbate, Flavor, Methylparaben, Cetylpyridinium chloride, Citric acid, Sucralose, Honey extract, Lactobacillus, Prunus persica (peach)In terms of ingredients, it's not too dissimilar from something like Crest Pro Health (I mention that one because that's the one that the rest of the family uses; I'm a Listerine user myself mainly). A couple of odd notes are the peach flavoring that I don't really get, and the addition of Lactobacillus. Lactobacillus could potentially be an oral probiotic, potentially aiding in cavity prevention, but it seems that research is still preliminary on that. Otherwise, nothing else really stands out to me in the ingredient list.It does swish and froth up really well, likely due to the castor oil (thankfully no sodium laureth sulfate in this stuff). Taste wise, it describes itself as a soft mint, but I think it's pretty strong myself, and that's coming from someone who used to pop Altoids like candy. My only real gripe is that the two packets I've used thus far haven't opened cleanly, so it took a pair of scissors. Otherwise, the actual mouthwash is really good. The box itself is a reusable plastic box, so traveling with something like this should be easy. All in all, good mouthwash, not so good packets.

reviews.reviewTitle: Doesn't Burn, Good Flavour, Fresh Breath On The Go!
reviews.reviewText: These are really perfect for me.I don't use mouthwash all the time especially mouthwash with alcohol.This way I have sealed individual packets that I can use at home or on the go without worrying about spilling or the space it takes for a huge bottle.These have a nice mint flavour and there is no burning at all.No fluoride is a plus for me too.These are absolutely small enough to carry on an airplane too.And the package is thick and sturdy so I know it won't break open.I also use these when my throat and mouth is a little dry, especially on long drives when I don't want to be drinking tons of water.I'm really happy I ordered these. They give me confidence with my breath and help alleviate dry mouth too.

reviews.reviewTitle: Great taste, icy cool freshness, very pricy
reviews.reviewText: Alcohol free and fluoride free, icy fresh minty tasting mouthwash, each packet 12 ml and there are 30 in total. These come in sturdy perforated packets that are easy to rip when need to and they stay closed when you dont, even when they're weighed down in a purse. Whether you want to use these up daily for a month, or have them in your bag at work to go, or even give them as little gifts at a dinner party, they will have multiple uses. These work great if you wear retainers at night and want fresh breath in the morning.It is very expensive though when you compare the cost of $3-5 for a big bottle that will last a family a couple of months, these packets come to $1 each for 12 ml one time use, yes the portability is great for travel, etc but they are pricy.

These mouthwash are individually packed which is very nice!Can be used anywhere, no rinsing required... so basically gargle for 20-30 seconds and spit it out!Taste is not too bad either. Feels minty fresh after using.Excellent for on-the-go mouthwash!
These individual mouthwash packs are great for traveling or even keep in your purse. The minty flavor leaves your mouth feeling refreshed.

Pretty standard tasting mouthwash, quite refreshing. We liked the packaging because of how convenient it was to bring on trips. The box comes with 30 packs so it's pretty much $1 per use which is quite expensive.
